deck: Lorenz Lammens (born February 6th 1974) is a Belgian creator and writer of comic books. He owns the art studio Octane Comics that finds, develops and publishes exciting new artists in the industry.
name: Lorenz Lammens

description:
Johnny Fraser-Allen is an acclaimed sculptor from New Zealand who has been working with Peter Jackson on his movies King Kong and The Hobbit trilogy. Fraser-Allen is also known for the award-winning The Gloaming Trilogy, an exhibition and series of sculptures inspired by fantasy books.

In 2014, he teamed up with Evangeline Lilly for her graphic novel debut, The Squickerwonkers, for which Fraser-Allen provided the illustrations.
name: Johnny Fraser-Allen

description: Jeff King is a producer and a writer. In television, he's worked on White Collar and Due South. His comic writing debut begins with DC's CONVERGENCE.
name: Jeff King
